data.chText: 废旧家具；不用的大件物品
data.enText: pieces of furniture, and other large objects that you do not use any more
a lumber room (= for storing lumber in)

data.chText: 缓慢吃力地移动；笨拙地行进
data.enText: to move in a slow, heavy and awkward way

data.chText: 一群大象迈着缓慢而沉重的步子从旁边经过。
data.enText: A family of elephants lumbered by.
to give sb a responsibility, etc., that they do not want and that they cannot get rid of

data.chText: 父母外出时，晚上姐姐就得照管我。
data.enText: When our parents went out, my sister got lumbered with me for the evening.

tr: an implement used in baseball by the batter
the wood of trees cut and prepared for use as building material
cut lumber, as in woods and forests

example: The heavy man lumbered across the room

value.def: Lumber consists of trees and large pieces of wood that have been roughly cut up.

example.ex: It was made of soft lumber, spruce by the look of it...
example.tran: 其制作材料是软木，看起来像是云杉。

example.ex: He was going to have to purchase all his lumber at full retail price.
example.tran: 他将不得不把所有木材按零售价分文不少地买下来。

value.def: If someone or something lumbers from one place to another, they move there very slowly and clumsily.

example.ex: He turned and lumbered back to his chair...
example.tran: 他转过身来，蹒跚着走回到椅子边坐下。

example.ex: The truck lumbered across the parking lot toward the road...
example.tran: 卡车隆隆地驶过停车场准备上路。

example.ex: He looked straight ahead and overtook a lumbering lorry.
example.tran: 他眼睛直视前方，加速超过了前面一辆慢吞吞行进的大卡车。
